title: Kate Moss braless in jumpsuit for Knightsbridge dinner | Daily Mail Online
text: Buy now Kate's good friend Enninful, a Ghana-born stylist who was formerly the youngest fashion director at i-D, also currently serves as W's Creative Director. Model Kate was of course one of W magazine's most recent cover stars, sharing special collector's issue shoot with Jennifer Lopez, Taraji P Henson, Jessica Chastain and Donatella Versace. The shoot went global as Kate posed completely naked inside, almost three decades after her modelling debut. Leggy lady: The catwalk queen was confident in mega high heels, too In the cover interview, Kate admitted that since the age of 16 she had grown accustomed to take her clothes off for photoshoots. 'From the beginning,' she said. 'Photographers always got me to take my clothes off, even though I don’t like my body at all. I just had to get comfortable with being naked.' On her determination within the modelling industry, Kate went on to say: 'I want to please the person behind the camera. I’m a hard worker. And I like the process of creating an image.' Late night: The mum-of-one looked weary as she left the venue Made up: With minimal make-up, Kate wore a striking red lipstick Share or comment on this article Most watched News videos
